  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba: \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0d8b\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0db7\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf \u0db1\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf?: \u0dad\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Easter Attack: Will President Ranil be removed from accountability or not?: The decision is overdue",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The seven-judge bench postponed until today (02) the announcement of the order on whether or not the current President Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe, who is named as a respondent in the fundamental rights petitions filed regarding the inevitability of the Easter Sunday attacks, will be removed from being a respondent in those petitions.",
        "These petitions were filed by Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya, Bhuvaneka Aluvihare, Priyantha Jayawardena, L. T. B. Dehideniya, Mild Fernando, S. These matters were presented during the hearing today (02) in front of a Supreme Court bench consisting of Mr. Turai Raja and Mr. Gamini Amarasekara.",
        "When this case was called, lawyer Mr. Suren Fernando, who appeared for the respondent President Ranil Wickramasinghe, stated that since the former Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe has been named as a respondent and has been elected as the current President, he informed the court that he should be removed as a respondent in these petitions.",
        "President's lawyer Salia Piris, President of the Sri Lanka Bar Association, who protested against it, stated that according to the 19th Amendment of the Constitution, the President has immunity only in civil and criminal cases and since these petitions are fundamental rights petitions, the existing cases against him should be continued. and that",
        "Mr. Shamil Perera, the President's lawyer who appeared in the court for Malcolm Cardinal Ranjith, the Archbishop of Colombo, stated that he agrees with the facts of the President's lawyer, Salia Peiris, and accordingly, the case against President Ranil Wickremesinghe should be continued.",
        "Additional Solicitor General Priyantha Nawana, who appeared in court on behalf of the Governor-General, stated that since the President is entitled to immunity under Article 35 (1) of the Constitution, he cannot be prosecuted either on an official or private level. Accordingly, the Additional Solicitor General further informed the court that the President named as the respondent in this petition should be released.",
        "Taking into consideration the facts presented, the court informed that the announcement of the order will be postponed until later."
      ],
